Lab 8

Code 
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import LinearDiscriminantAnalysis, QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier, export_text
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
from plotnine import *
Code 
df = pd.read_csv('https://www.dropbox.com/s/s2a1uoiegitupjc/cannabis_full.csv?raw=1')

PArt 1: Binary Classification

Code 
df_binary = df[df['Type'].isin(['sativa', 'indica'])].copy()
X_binary = df_binary.drop(['Strain', 'Type', 'Rating', 'Effects', 'Flavor'], axis=1)
y_binary = df_binary['Type']

Metric: Accuracy (balanced dataset with no specific target category)

Code 
lda_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='mean')),
    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('lda', LinearDiscriminantAnalysis())
])

lda_cv_scores = cross_val_score(lda_pipeline, X_binary, y_binary, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
print(f"LDA Cross-validated Accuracy: {lda_cv_scores.mean():.4f}")

lda_pipeline.fit(X_binary, y_binary)
y_pred_lda = lda_pipeline.predict(X_binary)
cm = confusion_matrix(y_binary, y_pred_lda)
cm_df = pd.DataFrame(cm, index=['indica', 'sativa'], columns=['indica', 'sativa'])
cm_df = cm_df.reset_index().melt(id_vars='index')
cm_df.columns = ['Actual', 'Predicted', 'Count']
(ggplot(cm_df, aes(x='Predicted', y='Actual', fill='Count')) +
 geom_tile() +
 geom_text(aes(label='Count')) +
 labs(title='LDA Confusion Matrix') +
 theme_minimal())
LDA Cross-validated Accuracy: 0.8446

SVC

Code 
svc_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='mean')),
    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('svc', SVC())
])

svc_param_grid = {
    'svc__C': [0.1, 1, 10],
    'svc__kernel': ['linear', 'rbf']
}

svc_grid = GridSearchCV(svc_pipeline, svc_param_grid, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
svc_grid.fit(X_binary, y_binary)

print(f"Best SVC parameters: {svc_grid.best_params_}")
print(f"SVC Cross-validated Accuracy: {svc_grid.best_score_:.4f}")

y_pred_svc = svc_grid.best_estimator_.predict(X_binary)
cm = confusion_matrix(y_binary, y_pred_svc)
cm_df = pd.DataFrame(cm, index=['indica', 'sativa'], columns=['indica', 'sativa'])
cm_df = cm_df.reset_index().melt(id_vars='index')
cm_df.columns = ['Actual', 'Predicted', 'Count']
(ggplot(cm_df, aes(x='Predicted', y='Actual', fill='Count')) +
 geom_tile() +
 geom_text(aes(label='Count')) +
 labs(title='SVC Confusion Matrix') +
 theme_minimal())
Best SVC parameters: {'svc__C': 0.1, 'svc__kernel': 'linear'}
SVC Cross-validated Accuracy: 0.8455

SVM

Code 
svm_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='mean')),
    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('svm', SVC(kernel='poly'))
])

svm_param_grid = {
    'svm__C': [0.1, 1, 10],
    'svm__degree': [2, 3, 4]
}

svm_grid = GridSearchCV(svm_pipeline, svm_param_grid, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
svm_grid.fit(X_binary, y_binary)

print(f"Best SVM parameters: {svm_grid.best_params_}")
print(f"SVM Cross-validated Accuracy: {svm_grid.best_score_:.4f}")

y_pred_svm = svm_grid.best_estimator_.predict(X_binary)
cm = confusion_matrix(y_binary, y_pred_svm)
cm_df = pd.DataFrame(cm, index=['indica', 'sativa'], columns=['indica', 'sativa'])
cm_df = cm_df.reset_index().melt(id_vars='index')
cm_df.columns = ['Actual', 'Predicted', 'Count']
(ggplot(cm_df, aes(x='Predicted', y='Actual', fill='Count')) +
 geom_tile() +
 geom_text(aes(label='Count')) +
 labs(title='SVM (Polynomial) Confusion Matrix') +
 theme_minimal())

Part Two: Natural Multiclass

Code 
X_full = df.drop(['Strain', 'Type', 'Rating', 'Effects', 'Flavor'], axis=1)
y_full = df['Type']

Question 1 Decison Tree

Code 
tree_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('tree', DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42))
])

tree_param_grid = {
    'tree__max_depth': [3, 5, 7, 10],
    'tree__min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
}

tree_grid = GridSearchCV(tree_pipeline, tree_param_grid, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
tree_grid.fit(X_full, y_full)

print(f"Best Decision Tree parameters: {tree_grid.best_params_}")
print(f"Decision Tree Cross-validated Accuracy: {tree_grid.best_score_:.4f}")

tree_rules = export_text(tree_grid.best_estimator_.named_steps['tree'], 
                         feature_names=list(X_full.columns))
print("\nDecision Tree Rules:")
print(tree_rules)
Best Decision Tree parameters: {'tree__max_depth': 3, 'tree__min_samples_split': 2}
Decision Tree Cross-validated Accuracy: 0.6172

Decision Tree Rules:
|--- Sleepy <= 0.50
|   |--- Energetic <= 0.50
|   |   |--- Pineapple <= nan
|   |   |   |--- class: sativa
|   |   |--- Pineapple >  nan
|   |   |   |--- class: hybrid
|   |--- Energetic >  0.50
|   |   |--- Relaxed <= 0.50
|   |   |   |--- class: sativa
|   |   |--- Relaxed >  0.50
|   |   |   |--- class: hybrid
|--- Sleepy >  0.50
|   |--- Citrus <= 0.50
|   |   |--- Uplifted <= 0.50
|   |   |   |--- class: indica
|   |   |--- Uplifted >  0.50
|   |   |   |--- class: indica
|   |--- Citrus >  0.50
|   |   |--- Sweet <= 0.50
|   |   |   |--- class: indica
|   |   |--- Sweet >  0.50
|   |   |   |--- class: hybrid

Sleepy is the most influencal varialbe when predicitng class.

KNN

Code 
knn_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='mean')),
    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('knn', KNeighborsClassifier())
])

knn_param_grid = {
    'knn__n_neighbors': [3, 5, 7, 9, 11]
}

knn_grid = GridSearchCV(knn_pipeline, knn_param_grid, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
knn_grid.fit(X_full, y_full)

print(f"Best KNN parameters: {knn_grid.best_params_}")
print(f"KNN Cross-validated Accuracy: {knn_grid.best_score_:.4f}")

y_pred_knn = knn_grid.best_estimator_.predict(X_full)
cm = confusion_matrix(y_full, y_pred_knn)
cm_df = pd.DataFrame(cm, index=['hybrid', 'indica', 'sativa'], columns=['hybrid', 'indica', 'sativa'])
cm_df = cm_df.reset_index().melt(id_vars='index')
cm_df.columns = ['Actual', 'Predicted', 'Count']
(ggplot(cm_df, aes(x='Predicted', y='Actual', fill='Count')) +
 geom_tile() +
 geom_text(aes(label='Count')) +
 labs(title='KNN Multiclass Confusion Matrix') +
 theme_minimal())
Best KNN parameters: {'knn__n_neighbors': 11}
KNN Cross-validated Accuracy: 0.5504

cm_df.columns = ['Actual', 'Predicted', 'Count']
(ggplot(cm_df, aes(x='Predicted', y='Actual', fill='Count')) +
 geom_tile() +
 geom_text(aes(label='Count')) +
 labs(title='Logistic Regression: Hybrid vs Not Hybrid') +
 theme_minimal())
Logistic Regression Hybrid vs Not: 0.6121

Question 2 Which of the six models did the best job distinguishing the target category from the rest? Which did the worst? Does this make intuitive sense?

The Logstic regression OvR - Sativa vs not Sativa model has the highest level of accuracy. The worst model was SVC OvR - Hybrid vs Not Hybrid. Yes this makes the most sense as for this type of problem, a LR is already a better choice and on top of that predicting sativa vs not sativa (two opposites) is much easier than predicting hybrid vs not hybrid, as non hyrbids of features of hybrids.

Code 
df_indica_sativa = df[df['Type'].isin(['indica', 'sativa'])].copy()

    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),
    ('svc', SVC())
])
